  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Markets are experiencing risk-on sentiment driven by cautious optimism around potential Iran peace talks and ceasefire extensions, with oil prices stabilizing below the $100 stagflation threshold. Bitcoin is testing key resistance near $75K while traditional assets climb to new highs as geopolitical tensions appear to be de-escalating.",
    "regimeImpact": "The relief rally thesis remains intact as geopolitical risk premium unwinds and oil stays contained, but we're approaching critical resistance levels that could define the next phase.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Monitor BMNR $62,300 structural level closely as BTC approaches $75K resistance - consider tightening cash-secured put strikes if momentum stalls",
      "Prepare to reduce Maturity sector overweight if peace deal materializes and growth assets regain momentum above key technical levels",
      "Watch for VIX compression below 25 and HYG strength above $80 to confirm risk-on rotation sustainability"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Oil prices stabilizing with focus on diplomatic efforts reduces stagflation risk and supports risk asset recovery.",
      "Bitcoin testing $75K-$78K resistance zone while retail remains bearish and institutions accumulate on dips.",
      "Dollar weakness on Fed independence concerns and peace hopes supports risk assets and crypto momentum.",
      "Traditional markets hitting new highs suggests broad risk-on sentiment that could lift crypto if geopolitical clarity emerges."
    ]
